# Cloudflare Pages SPA Redirects
# Cloudflare Pages serves static assets BEFORE these rules. But during edge
# cold-start, a missing-from-cache asset would fall through to /* and get
# served as index.html (text/html) — causing strict-MIME module-script errors
# in the browser. Force 404 on missing /assets/* so Vite's chunk loader can
# trigger a hard reload instead of executing HTML as JavaScript.
/assets/*  /404.html  404

/static/*  /static/:splat  200
/icons/*   /icons/:splat   200
/service-worker.js  /service-worker.js  200
/sw.js  /sw.js  200
/manifest.webmanifest  /manifest.webmanifest  200
/registerSW.js  /registerSW.js  200

# SPA fallback - all other routes go to index.html
/*  /index.html  200
